# S3 security & encryption

## Layered access — private by default

- **Block Public Access** — on by default; **overrides any public grant**, runs first
- **Bucket policy** — resource-based, cross-account / conditional
- **IAM policy** — same-account principals
- **ACLs** — legacy, off since 2023

**Explicit deny anywhere wins.** BPA is the "oops, public bucket" safety net.

## Encryption — default on since 2023

- **SSE-S3** — AWS keys — the default baseline
- **SSE-KMS** — your key, **CloudTrail-logged** — regulated data
- **SSE-C** — you send the key · **Client-side** — AWS sees only ciphertext

**Bucket Keys** cut KMS calls ~99%. Enforce HTTPS via `aws:SecureTransport`.
